<h2 id="scheduling-metrics">Rule 1: Track These 7 Scheduling Metrics Daily</h2>

<div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
<p>Top HVAC companies measure what matters. They track seven core metrics every single day, not just monthly reports that arrive too late to fix problems.</p>

<p><strong>Jobs per tech per day:</strong> Elite companies average 6.8-7.5 jobs per tech for mixed service work. Emergency-focused operations hit 9-12 jobs daily. Companies below 5.5 jobs per tech lose $12,000+ annually per technician.</p>

<p><strong>Drive time percentage:</strong> Best-in-class companies keep total drive time under 18% of the workday. Companies exceeding 25% drive time waste 1.2 hours daily per tech. That's $24,000 in lost billable time annually per technician at $100/hour rates.</p>

<p><strong>First-call completion rate:</strong> Top performers complete 87-92% of jobs on the first visit. Each return trip costs $45-65 in drive time and reduces daily job capacity by one appointment.</p>
</div>

