<p><strong>Revenue per billable hour:</strong> Elite companies generate $140-180 per billable hour. This metric reveals scheduling efficiency better than total daily revenue because it accounts for drive time and job complexity.</p>

<p><strong>Schedule fill rate:</strong> Top companies maintain 92-96% schedule utilization. Empty appointment slots cost $85-120 per hour in lost opportunity. Companies with poor scheduling systems waste 8-12 hours weekly per tech in unfilled time.</p>

<p><strong>Emergency integration time:</strong> The best dispatchers integrate emergency calls within 45 minutes while maintaining existing appointments. Poor integration creates 2+ hour delays and customer complaints.</p>

<p><strong>Customer callback rate:</strong> Elite companies see 3-5% callback rates within 48 hours of service completion. Higher rates indicate poor job quality or inadequate initial diagnosis.</p>
