<h2 id="no-show-prevention">Rule 3: Triple-Touch Confirmation System</h2>

<div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
<p>Elite HVAC companies maintain 6-8% no-show rates through systematic customer confirmation. Industry average sits at 14-18% no-shows, costing the typical company $8,500-12,000 annually per technician.</p>

<p><strong>48-Hour Confirmation Call:</strong> First touch happens 48 hours before the appointment. Office staff confirms the time, provides arrival window, and captures any access issues (locked gates, dogs, parking restrictions). This call reduces no-shows by 35-40%.</p>

<p><strong>Morning-Of Text Reminder:</strong> Second touch is an automated SMS sent between 7-9 AM on appointment day. Include tech name, arrival window, and direct contact number. Add weather warnings for outdoor unit work ("Today's service requires outdoor access - please clear path to unit").</p>

<p><strong>30-Minute Warning Call:</strong> Third touch happens when the tech is 30 minutes away. This call confirms the customer is home and ready. It prevents the costly scenario where techs arrive to empty houses or locked businesses.</p>
</div>

